A student died while four were admitted after they drank ethanol at a school in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu.The boys had gone for a chemistry lesson. They complained of pain before they were taken to Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital."Some of the students decided to drink the chemical without the knowledge of teachers leading to this unfortunate loss of life," said a teacher who did not want to be named.School principal Nareo Kiptingei said the group drank the chemical two days ago.Police and senior education officials have visited the school to launch investigations.They said the students were in critical condition.Nareo said: "We have given full information to the authorities and the Education ministry. They are the ones authorised to talk to the media."